===Etymology===
Old English ''[[heafod|hēafod]]'', from Proto-Germanic ''*khaubuthan'', from Proto-Indo-European ''*kauput-'' ('head', 'bowl').  Cognate with German ''[[Haupt]]'', Dutch ''[[hoofd]]'', Swedish ''[[huvud]]''; the Indo-European root is also the source of Latin ''[[caput]]''.

